name: Air Fryer Catfish Nuggets
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: Crispy fried catfish without the guilt of deep frying. Serve with tartar or cocktail sauce for dipping.
ingredients: 1 pound catfish fillets, cut into 1 inch pieces
3/4 cup seasoned fish fry coating (such as Louisiana® Fish Fry Products)
directions: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Place seasoned breading mix in a gallon-size plastic resealable bag
Drop catfish pieces inside, close, and shake to coat fish with breading on all sides
Spread out nuggets on a baking sheet and spray with non-stick cooking spray
Place nuggets in an even layer in the air fryer basket, sprayed side down
You may need to work in batches depending on the size of your air fryer
Spray the tops with non-stick cooking spray
Using tongs, flip nuggets over and cook for 4 minutes more
